text = "label"

result = ''.join(chr(ord(c) ^ 13) for c in text)

print(result)


'''
What’s happening in code
ord(c)

👉 char → number

^ 13

👉 XOR operation

chr(...)

👉 number → char

..........
XOR = bit flipping controlled by another number

Why XOR is powerful??

Because of this property:

A ^ B ^ B = A

👉 XOR twice with same value → original back

Example:

c ^ 13 ^ 13 = c

👉 This is why XOR is used in encryption

'''